Many KBs grow steadily. Wikidata, for instance, contained 20M statements in 2015, but 1.2B statements in 2023, hinting at a substantial increase of its recall. Reality, on the other hand, evolves as well, which may mean that areas formerly complete might become incomplete later on. In this section, we discuss formalisms for temporal annotations, methods for extraction and extrapolation, and observational studies concerning recall trends.